      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions (hematocrit, temperature, blood analog rheology, pump speed, flow rate) documented and traceable to COU operating envelope with uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "Flow rate and pump speed are well-documented. Hematocrit was fixed at 33% and temperature at 37°C but uncertainty in these parameters was not propagated through the hemolysis model. Blood analog rheology deviates from clinical VAD blood properties. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
