      "rationale": "Mean absolute error of 12.4% is reported but the validation metric does not incorporate experimental measurement uncertainty bars in a formal statistical comparison. Coverage of all five operating points is confirmed. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI (hemolysis index) directly maps to the clinical endpoint; power-law model coefficients calibrated for human red blood cells under VAD shear histories.",
      "rationale": "The modified index of hemolysis (MIH) is the reported QoI and maps to clinical hemolysis risk. However, the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law coefficients were derived from bovine RBC data; human RBC coefficients are not used. This reduces relevance. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
